article.headline: James Madison 64, Delaware 50
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Rayshawn Goins had 15 points and 13 rebounds for his fifth double-double of the season and 11th of his career as James Madison defeated Colonial Athletic Association rival Delaware 64-50 Wednesday night. James Madison (10-10, 4-3) coach Matt Brady picked up his 150th career victory. A.J. Davis added 16 points off the bench on 7-of-11 shooting for the Dukes, while freshman Andre Nation had 12, including 10 in the first half, and Devon Moore had 10. Devon Saddler led Delaware (8-11, 3-3) with 16 points, six rebounds and three assists while Jarvis Threatt went 9 for 12 at the foul line to finish with 12 points. Jamelle Hagins, who last year had 23 points and 18 boards against James Madison, had just four points and four rebounds Wednesday. James Madison used a pair of 12-0 first-half runs to take a 29-18 halftime lead and never looked back.
